icit member-access/call levels\n- **File**: doc/ledger3.texi#L9963-L9994\n- **Category**: Documentation\n- **Confidence**: 75\n- **Problem**: The table is structurally correct against `parser.cc` (call → dot → unary → mul → add → comparison → and → or → ?: → comma → lambda → assign → semi). But the doc lists \"member access\" tighter than \"function call\", whereas `parse_dot_expr` calls `parse_call_expr` (parser.cc:129), making call **tighter** than dot. Verified: `f().x` parses as `(f()).x` — call binds first.\n- **Impact**: A close reader might think `a.b()` parses as `a.(b())`, when in fact it parses as `(a.b)()` since the dot loop in `parse_dot_expr` calls `parse_call_expr` for the right-hand side and then re-enters the dot loop.\n- **Fix**: Swap the order in the table: `function call` row should appear above `member access`. (Effect on real code is mostly nil for ordinary chains, but the table should match the parser.)\n\n---\n\n## Items verified correct\n- Type hierarchy `VOID &lt; BOOLEAN &lt; DATETIME &lt; DATE &lt; INTEGER &lt; AMOUNT &lt; BALANCE &lt; STRING &lt; MASK &lt; SEQUENCE` matches `src/value.h:64-65` (the doc trims `SCOPE`/`ANY` which is reasonable).\n- Single-letter aliases `m`, `P`, `U`, `S`, `t`, `T` at report scope all resolve correctly (src/report.cc:1722-1734).\n- `def`/`define` and `eval`/`expr` directive synonyms verified (src/textual_directives.cc:1069, 1079).\n- `assert`/`check`/`value` directives verified (src/textual_directives.cc:644, 635).\n- `==~` (EMATCH) operator and capture-group sequence semantics verified.\n- `account()` returning a scope-value verified (src/account.cc:306-322).\n- `options` lookup verified (src/report.cc:1858).\n- `top_amount`, `truncate`/`truncated`, `commodity`, `magnitude`, `value_date`, `display_amount`/`display_total`, `min`/`max`/`int`/`str` (in session.cc:508-521), `fifo_lots`/`lifo_lots`, `is_seq`, `get_at` — all bindings exist as documented.\n\nThe chapter is in good shape overall. The `count`/`subcount` swap is the most important fix because it's a factual error a user will hit on first try.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>126420</total_tokens><tool_uses>99</tool_uses><duration_ms>538009</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>",
