            "content": "Address deep-review findings on Value Expressions chapter (#804)\n\nThe deep-review pass against the C++ source uncovered several factual\nerrors and stylistic inconsistencies in the new chapter.  This commit\naddresses them and adds a regression test that pins down the\ndocumented semantics for future changes.\n\nSource-truth corrections:\n\n* count/subcount semantics were documented backwards.  Verified\n  empirically and against src/account.cc:521,602 (count and N bind to\n  cumulative get_count) versus src/account.cc:573,587 (subcount and n\n  bind to own-postings get_subcount).  Rewrote the n / count / N /\n  subcount entry to describe both scopes correctly.\n\n* The scope chain claim wrongly inserted xact_t between post_t and\n  item_t.  In fact src/post.cc:701,838 falls through directly to\n  item_t::lookup; the parent transaction is not in the chain (which is\n  why post.cc duplicates xact-level fields like code, payee, and\n  magnitude).  Updated the Names and Scope text accordingly.\n\n* parent in posting scope returns the enclosing transaction\n  (src/post.cc:788), not the account hierarchy parent.  Added the\n  posting-scope meaning to the @defvar parent entry.\n\n* null is a built-in identifier (resolved through report_t::lookup as\n  fn_null), not a literal keyword like true/false.  It can be shadowed\n  by user definition; true/false cannot.  Moved null out of the\n  keywords paragraph and described it as an identifier.\n\nOther corrections:\n\n* Replaced the missing @node for \"Debugging expressions and queries\"\n  with @subheading, which does not require a node.\n\n* Fixed the self-referential @ref{Member Access} that pointed at the\n  same section it appeared in; the options example now references the\n  Binary Operators section (where the reused journal actually lives)\n  and the duplicated @smallexample output block was removed.\n\n* Converted British spellings (recognises, flavoured, unrealised,\n  colour, honoured, commoditised) to American to match the rest of the\n  manual.  The two pre-existing instances in unrelated sections of\n  ledger3.texi are left for a future pass.\n\n* Replaced @comma{} inside @samp{} with literal commas; @comma{} is\n  only required in nested @xref-style argument contexts.\n\n* Restored alphabetical order: lifo_lots moved after justify, truncate\n  moved after truncated, virtual moved after value_date.\n\n* Noted that index is a posting-only alias (account scope only binds\n  n and count, per src/account.cc).\n\n* Removed two redundant ,with_input:HASH self-references on examples\n  whose own input block already provides the data.\n\nNew test:\n\n* test/regress/804.test locks down the n / index / count / N /\n  subcount / parent claims with concrete expected outputs from a\n  three-posting fixture, so a future change to account.cc or post.cc\n  that breaks the documented semantics will fail this test.\n\nAll 9 existing in-chapter doc-tests still pass; makeinfo build is\nclean (only the pre-existing Valuation cross-reference warnings).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n",
